1
00:01:07,440 --> 00:01:16,000
My friend Barry

2
00:01:29,720 --> 00:01:30,720
I'm telling you,

3
00:01:30,880 --> 00:01:33,200
that creature's fooling us.

4
00:01:33,400 --> 00:01:34,520
There are still traces.

5
00:01:35,120 --> 00:01:37,120
We won't be fooled any longer.

6
00:01:39,280 --> 00:01:40,400
Give me the goat.

7
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:41,600
Here.

8
00:01:50,920 --> 00:01:51,880
Not like that!

9
00:01:52,040 --> 00:01:53,240
Why not like that?

10
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:54,480
Not like this.

11
00:01:54,600 --> 00:01:56,080
-Sideways!
-The wolf doesn't care!

12
00:01:56,240 --> 00:01:57,280
Are you kidding me?

13
00:01:57,440 --> 00:01:59,000
We'll catch him this time!

14
00:02:35,560 --> 00:02:37,200
We got him!

15
00:03:00,080 --> 00:03:02,400
You're hungry too, aren't you?

16
00:03:10,800 --> 00:03:11,800
Come!

17
00:03:15,600 --> 00:03:16,680
-I'm coming!
-We got him!

18
00:03:32,360 --> 00:03:33,880
Goddammit!

19
00:03:34,040 --> 00:03:35,120
Impossible!

20
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:37,000
Come on!

21
00:03:37,560 --> 00:03:38,560
That's enough!

22
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:40,520
Come. Enough is enough!

23
00:04:00,240 --> 00:04:02,000
Where have you been?

24
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:03,200
I was worried.

25
00:04:03,320 --> 00:04:04,480
I fought a wolf!

26
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:06,440
Yeah, right...

27
00:04:06,640 --> 00:04:07,720
Sure!

28
00:04:08,480 --> 00:04:10,000
And I even won!

29
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:23,640
Tomorrow will be another tough day.

30
00:04:24,280 --> 00:04:26,760
Can't we rest a little longer here?

31
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:31,960
Come on, we're almost there.

32
00:04:32,720 --> 00:04:34,480
One more day until we reach the pass,

33
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:36,200
then another day or two

34
00:04:36,360 --> 00:04:38,080
on the other side into the valley.

35
00:04:38,360 --> 00:04:39,960
And then we're at the sea.

36
00:04:41,320 --> 00:04:42,800
Then we're in Italy.

37
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,000
Where it's warm.

38
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:51,320
There are no soldiers there?

39
00:04:52,120 --> 00:04:54,120
No French people, that's for sure.

40
00:04:54,840 --> 00:04:56,240
And if they do show up,

41
00:04:57,520 --> 00:04:59,480
the Austrians will kick their asses!

42
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:00,760
Good.

43
00:05:04,000 --> 00:05:05,360
We'll find work.

44
00:05:05,880 --> 00:05:07,360
The rich people in the big cities

45
00:05:07,520 --> 00:05:09,160
-need servants.
-Servants?

46
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:10,520
Yes.

47
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:13,480
We're getting our own room.

48
00:05:13,720 --> 00:05:14,800
Just for the two of us.

49
00:05:15,080 --> 00:05:16,200
A real bed.

50
00:05:17,000 --> 00:05:17,960
And you...

51
00:05:18,320 --> 00:05:19,840
You'll even get a new scarf.

52
00:05:23,680 --> 00:05:25,200
Tell me about the sea.

53
00:05:28,080 --> 00:05:30,080
It's bigger than where we live, right?

54
00:05:30,360 --> 00:05:32,600
Bigger than Lake Lucerne.

55
00:05:34,120 --> 00:05:35,760
A hundred times bigger.

56
00:05:36,320 --> 00:05:37,320
So big

57
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:39,480
that you can't see the other shore.

58
00:05:44,840 --> 00:05:46,520
And there are fish

59
00:05:46,760 --> 00:05:48,200
as big as calves...

60
00:05:50,760 --> 00:05:52,400
And it's warm.

61
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,720
And when you lie on your back

62
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:56,360
and stretch out your arms,

63
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:58,360
the water will carry you all by itself.

64
00:05:59,880 --> 00:06:02,680
We just have to get
over the pass tomorrow.

65
00:06:03,000 --> 00:06:06,440
And then we'll have
a better life in Italy.

66
00:06:21,640 --> 00:06:23,320
We can do it.

67
00:06:23,760 --> 00:06:24,760
Come on!

68
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:45,000
Austrian soldiers.

69
00:06:45,200 --> 00:06:46,200
What are they doing here?

70
00:06:46,360 --> 00:06:48,720
Kick the asses of the French, right?

71
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:52,720
Are you okay?

72
00:06:53,000 --> 00:06:54,480
We're almost there.

73
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:13,600
Alfons!

74
00:07:18,840 --> 00:07:20,480
I can't go on anymore!

75
00:07:22,480 --> 00:07:23,560
Let me see.

76
00:08:30,480 --> 00:08:31,440
Finally!

77
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:37,200
Where am I?

78
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:38,480
In the hospice.

79
00:08:38,640 --> 00:08:40,360
You slept for two days straight.

80
00:08:49,000 --> 00:08:50,360
Where's Alfons?

81
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:54,640
I have to take you to the kitchen

82
00:08:54,840 --> 00:08:55,800
as soon as you're awake.

83
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,320
You're awake now!

84
00:08:59,760 --> 00:09:01,080
Put your clothes on.

85
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:03,080
I'll wait outside.

86
00:09:27,720 --> 00:09:28,960
Come on now!

87
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:38,240
Did you try to steal again?

88
00:09:38,440 --> 00:09:40,680
-You're getting fatter and fatter!
-Come, Patch, come.

89
00:09:41,280 --> 00:09:42,280
Come.

90
00:09:42,480 --> 00:09:44,000
The kitchen is this way.

91
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:03,720
-Hi.
-Hello, Resi.

92
00:10:03,880 --> 00:10:04,840
This is my father.

93
00:10:05,040 --> 00:10:08,120
His dogs are the best avalanche dogs
in the world.

94
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:10,360
They've saved many lives.

95
00:10:11,600 --> 00:10:13,960
Come! I have to take you to the kitchen.

96
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:19,200
Hurry up before they do
something stupid.

97
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:20,600
Resi!

98
00:10:22,520 --> 00:10:23,600
I need a new bandage.

99
00:10:23,800 --> 00:10:24,880
Come in the afternoon.

100
00:10:25,040 --> 00:10:26,520
Brother Medicus will be back then.

101
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:29,360
But it's already quite loose.

102
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:31,000
It won't heal properly like that.

103
00:10:31,160 --> 00:10:32,160
This tiny cut?

104
00:10:32,520 --> 00:10:34,760
Just leave alone,
then it'll heal by itself.

105
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:38,000
-Where's Alfons?
-Who?

106
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:39,640
Alfons, my brother.

107
00:10:39,920 --> 00:10:41,280
-Hey!
-Great shot.

108
00:10:41,440 --> 00:10:43,400
Come on, leave those monkeys alone.

109
00:10:57,000 --> 00:10:58,080
Brother Pietro.

110
00:10:58,880 --> 00:10:59,840
Hello, my dear!

111
00:11:00,000 --> 00:11:01,320
He needs a warm soup.

112
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:02,720
Sure!

113
00:11:02,880 --> 00:11:04,840
Go ahead, give it to him.

114
00:11:05,200 --> 00:11:06,240
I don't have time.

115
00:11:08,000 --> 00:11:09,120
A bowl of soup!

116
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:12,080
Resi is a lovely girl, but...

117
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:13,600
How do you say...

118
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:15,480
She's a stubborn girl.

119
00:11:16,880 --> 00:11:17,920
What's your name?

120
00:11:18,080 --> 00:11:19,080
George.

121
00:11:19,760 --> 00:11:20,880
Sit down.

122
00:11:22,880 --> 00:11:24,360
A good soup...

123
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:28,320
Here you go... enjoy!

124
00:11:29,080 --> 00:11:30,040
Eat!

125
00:11:30,200 --> 00:11:32,240
And then we'll see what we do with you.

126
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:34,200
I want to see my brother.

127
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:35,720
Your brother?

128
00:11:37,520 --> 00:11:38,560
Yes.

129
00:11:38,760 --> 00:11:40,600
We arrived two days ago.

130
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:42,120
What?

131
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:44,360
Your brother...
They all left for Italy.

132
00:11:44,560 --> 00:11:45,560
Two days ago.

133
00:11:46,240 --> 00:11:47,240
No!

134
00:11:49,800 --> 00:11:52,000
Sonny!
Your soup...

135
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:53,240
Alfons!

136
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:56,600
Alfons!

137
00:12:02,880 --> 00:12:05,000
Alfons!

138
00:12:06,280 --> 00:12:08,240
Alfons!

139
00:12:10,520 --> 00:12:12,880
Alfons!

140
00:12:38,160 --> 00:12:39,720
You wanted to see me, Prior?

141
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:41,640
I'm supposed to be in the library.

142
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:45,120
That's the boy from the last trek.

143
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:48,120
His brother has
travelled on without him.

144
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:49,640
Where is he from?

145
00:12:51,520 --> 00:12:52,720
Emmental.

146
00:12:53,080 --> 00:12:54,960
Emmental, Prior.

147
00:12:56,040 --> 00:12:58,000
His name is George.

148
00:12:58,160 --> 00:12:59,600
I want to go to Italy.

149
00:12:59,720 --> 00:13:00,720
To my brother.

150
00:13:00,880 --> 00:13:02,440
They boy's crazy.

151
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:05,200
You can't cross the pass on your own.

152
00:13:05,480 --> 00:13:07,440
I'll wait for the next trek.

153
00:13:07,640 --> 00:13:10,080
This was the last
trek you travelled with.

154
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:11,320
Until spring.

155
00:13:11,600 --> 00:13:12,760
Until spring?

156
00:13:13,120 --> 00:13:15,600
That means...
-That means you're staying here

157
00:13:15,800 --> 00:13:17,240
till the snow has melted.

158
00:13:19,240 --> 00:13:20,480
What about your parents?

159
00:13:26,360 --> 00:13:28,520
Your name is George, right?

160
00:13:30,160 --> 00:13:32,360
George,
you'll make yourself useful here.

161
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:35,480
Brother Pietro is always happy
to have extra help.

162
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:37,800
Work never stops up here.

163
00:13:39,120 --> 00:13:41,360
Is there any way to accommodate the boy?

164
00:13:42,120 --> 00:13:45,040
-You mean... in the novices' quarters?
-Yes.

165
00:13:45,600 --> 00:13:46,720
Heavens above...

166
00:13:46,960 --> 00:13:48,040
There's no free bed?

167
00:13:48,200 --> 00:13:49,680
Prior, with all due respect,

168
00:13:49,880 --> 00:13:52,600
we can't put a farm boy with
the novices. It'll cause unrest.

169
00:13:52,800 --> 00:13:54,280
Our discipline! How will

170
00:13:54,440 --> 00:13:56,200
the parents and patrons react when...

171
00:13:56,360 --> 00:13:59,280
I. I will find a place for him.

172
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:03,160
Fine.

173
00:14:05,400 --> 00:14:09,040
George, you'll do the jobs given to you.

174
00:14:09,240 --> 00:14:11,120
You help out where help is needed.

175
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:14,640
Okay?
Our job is to serve.

176
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:18,960
I expect diligence,
obedience and humility.

177
00:14:19,320 --> 00:14:21,720
You will fit in while you are with us.

178
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:23,480
Do you understand that?

179
00:16:15,360 --> 00:16:17,280
You guys are huge!

180
00:16:20,480 --> 00:16:23,800
It's okay, I won't hurt you.

181
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:29,720
I've never seen such big,
beautiful dogs.

182
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:37,880
I won't hurt you.

183
00:16:43,280 --> 00:16:45,240
Yes. Everything's fine.

184
00:17:14,760 --> 00:17:16,840
What a lively bunch you are!

185
00:17:17,200 --> 00:17:19,360
Hey, don't bite.

186
00:17:22,240 --> 00:17:23,240
Hey, you.

187
00:17:24,360 --> 00:17:25,880
You cheeky bugger!

188
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,960
What's wrong with you?

189
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:01,560
Is something wrong?

190
00:18:09,840 --> 00:18:11,760
You're so weak!

191
00:18:45,760 --> 00:18:46,720
Dad!

192
00:18:52,360 --> 00:18:55,520
Voilà. Come!
Get out of there!

193
00:18:56,720 --> 00:18:57,880
You can't sleep here.

194
00:18:58,080 --> 00:19:00,200
And certainly not in the litter box.

195
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:04,240
Yes, Stella.

196
00:19:05,240 --> 00:19:06,760
The mother can be very dangerous

197
00:19:06,960 --> 00:19:09,080
if you get too close to her puppies.

198
00:19:09,440 --> 00:19:10,440
Yes, I know

199
00:19:10,560 --> 00:19:12,640
but it kept me warm.

200
00:19:19,440 --> 00:19:22,080
This isn't a dormitory!
It's a stable.

201
00:19:32,120 --> 00:19:34,000
Why isn't he drinking?

202
00:19:37,720 --> 00:19:39,920
He can't fight for his place.

203
00:19:40,720 --> 00:19:42,440
The others keep pushing him away

204
00:19:42,600 --> 00:19:44,560
and he's getting weaker and weaker.

205
00:19:50,000 --> 00:19:51,760
He probably won't survive.

206
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:06,880
Who gave you this ammonite?

207
00:20:07,040 --> 00:20:08,760
It's a stone snail.

208
00:20:09,320 --> 00:20:11,000
That's a fossil.

209
00:20:11,360 --> 00:20:14,600
Of an animal that lived on earth
a long time ago.

210
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:18,000
It's a lucky charm.

211
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:20,360
Alfons gave it to me.

212
00:20:21,360 --> 00:20:23,320
And it's a stone snail!

213
00:20:29,160 --> 00:20:31,240
Where did they assign you to work?

214
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:33,240
With Brother Pietro.

215
00:20:35,120 --> 00:20:36,600
You'll help me with the dogs,

216
00:20:36,880 --> 00:20:38,240
when you're done in the kitchen.

217
00:20:39,240 --> 00:20:40,240
George, right?

218
00:20:41,120 --> 00:20:42,120
Julien.

219
00:20:51,200 --> 00:20:54,120
Here you go, something delicious.

220
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:56,160
Not so fast!

221
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:16,480
Did you eat the scraps yourself?

222
00:21:17,960 --> 00:21:18,960
Leave me alone!

223
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:22,360
Oh, thank you!

224
00:21:24,000 --> 00:21:25,920
Can I take the boy along with me?

225
00:21:26,560 --> 00:21:28,680
I'll bring him back, don't worry.

226
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:30,000
Alright.

227
00:21:30,480 --> 00:21:31,480
George.

228
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:33,000
Come!

229
00:21:35,520 --> 00:21:36,600
Go ahead!

230
00:21:37,520 --> 00:21:38,680
You go on.

231
00:21:38,840 --> 00:21:39,840
Me?

232
00:21:40,160 --> 00:21:41,440
I have to peel onions?

233
00:21:41,640 --> 00:21:43,080
Work is work.

234
00:21:49,560 --> 00:21:51,280
Lord, help me.

235
00:21:57,720 --> 00:21:58,760
Watch out!

236
00:21:58,960 --> 00:22:01,360
You have to walk close to the wall here.

237
00:22:03,360 --> 00:22:06,120
So, what happens with him now?

238
00:22:06,280 --> 00:22:07,280
With whom?

239
00:22:07,880 --> 00:22:10,560
With Stella's puppy
that's not getting any milk.

240
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:14,120
It won't survive.

241
00:22:14,280 --> 00:22:16,360
And Stella will eat him.

242
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:26,000
Nature does what it has to do.

243
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:29,200
Enough talk.

244
00:22:29,640 --> 00:22:30,840
Work is calling.

245
00:22:58,040 --> 00:22:59,040
Come.

246
00:23:11,920 --> 00:23:13,880
I'll bring him back, Stella.

247
00:23:14,640 --> 00:23:16,760
I can't just let him die.

248
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:41,880
What on earth are you doing?

249
00:23:42,200 --> 00:23:43,440
Why aren't you sleeping?

250
00:23:44,520 --> 00:23:45,640
Get out of here!

251
00:23:48,960 --> 00:23:50,680
How cute!

252
00:23:54,680 --> 00:23:57,480
What are you doing
with him in my kitchen?

253
00:23:57,880 --> 00:23:59,120
Julien says

254
00:23:59,440 --> 00:24:00,920
that he's going to die.

255
00:24:01,280 --> 00:24:03,560
Because nature does what it has to do.

256
00:24:03,920 --> 00:24:05,720
Nature. Nature

257
00:24:05,960 --> 00:24:07,840
doesn't know everything.

258
00:24:08,120 --> 00:24:09,480
Wait a minute.

259
00:24:27,800 --> 00:24:28,720
There!

260
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:30,720
Now take him back to the stable.

261
00:24:31,280 --> 00:24:32,240
Thank you!

262
00:24:38,640 --> 00:24:39,640
Come.

263
00:24:40,160 --> 00:24:41,480
You need to drink.

264
00:24:41,680 --> 00:24:44,480
I promised your mother
that you wouldn't die.

265
00:24:46,600 --> 00:24:47,600
Here.

266
00:25:02,120 --> 00:25:03,120
George?

267
00:25:04,200 --> 00:25:05,200
Yes?

268
00:25:08,880 --> 00:25:10,200
We have to get firewood.

269
00:25:10,400 --> 00:25:12,680
-What! Now?
-Yes, now!

270
00:25:12,840 --> 00:25:15,000
Brother Pietro will
get very angry if there

271
00:25:15,200 --> 00:25:18,480
-isn't enough wood in the kitchen
tomorrow morning. -Okay.

272
00:25:23,560 --> 00:25:24,720
What's the matter?

273
00:25:25,000 --> 00:25:26,080
I'm coming.

274
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:28,360
I can't wait forever!

275
00:25:34,720 --> 00:25:36,720
Let's try again later.

276
00:25:37,840 --> 00:25:39,360
I'll be right back.

277
00:25:50,120 --> 00:25:51,240
Hey, Matteo!

278
00:25:51,520 --> 00:25:52,640
What are you doing?

279
00:25:52,880 --> 00:25:54,200
You can't do that!

280
00:25:54,400 --> 00:25:55,360
Let me out!

281
00:25:56,640 --> 00:25:58,880
I have to get out of here! Hey!

282
00:26:00,400 --> 00:26:03,000
You'd rather be
with the pigs in the barn, right?

283
00:26:03,600 --> 00:26:05,720
But maybe they don't want you there.

284
00:26:06,000 --> 00:26:07,080
Let me out!

285
00:26:08,840 --> 00:26:10,240
Here you go, an onion.

286
00:26:10,480 --> 00:26:11,560
Unpeeled.

287
00:26:11,720 --> 00:26:12,800
In case you get hungry.

288
00:26:16,040 --> 00:26:17,040
Hey!

289
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:18,200
Matteo!

290
00:26:18,320 --> 00:26:19,320
Sorry.

291
00:26:19,440 --> 00:26:21,080
You have to let me out.

292
00:26:21,880 --> 00:26:22,880
Matteo!

293
00:26:23,000 --> 00:26:24,120
I have to get out of here!

294
00:26:28,080 --> 00:26:29,560
Let me out!

295
00:26:31,760 --> 00:26:33,480
Let me out!

296
00:27:07,520 --> 00:27:08,480
Wait!

297
00:27:08,640 --> 00:27:09,600
Leave me alone.

298
00:27:11,400 --> 00:27:13,360
Please don't tell on me!

299
00:27:18,640 --> 00:27:20,000
You're still alive!

300
00:27:28,000 --> 00:27:29,720
Go ahead, drink!

301
00:27:32,360 --> 00:27:34,960
You're drinking. Great!

302
00:27:58,840 --> 00:28:00,000
Sonny!

303
00:28:00,400 --> 00:28:01,520
Where were you?

304
00:28:02,240 --> 00:28:03,200
I'm sorry.

305
00:28:03,520 --> 00:28:04,520
I overslept.

306
00:28:04,640 --> 00:28:05,640
No!

307
00:28:05,840 --> 00:28:07,400
Not in my kitchen!

308
00:28:08,480 --> 00:28:10,720
No dawdling in my kitchen.

309
00:28:11,720 --> 00:28:12,960
Got it?

310
00:28:14,440 --> 00:28:15,440
Go!

311
00:28:27,240 --> 00:28:28,480
Thank you.

312
00:29:08,880 --> 00:29:10,000
What?

313
00:29:10,240 --> 00:29:11,720
You stole it?

314
00:29:13,480 --> 00:29:15,000
I helped him.

315
00:29:15,640 --> 00:29:17,080
But Dad said...

316
00:29:18,120 --> 00:29:19,720
Stella didn't eat him!

317
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:21,480
He was with you the whole time!

318
00:29:23,120 --> 00:29:25,000
Wait! Where are you going?

319
00:29:25,360 --> 00:29:26,840
I have to tell my dad.

320
00:29:27,360 --> 00:29:28,320
Can't you...?

321
00:29:29,480 --> 00:29:31,000
I have to feed him.

322
00:29:31,280 --> 00:29:32,720
He's not strong enough yet.

323
00:29:57,320 --> 00:29:58,760
Have you given him a name yet?

324
00:29:59,520 --> 00:30:00,480
A name?

325
00:30:00,880 --> 00:30:02,240
Yes, he needs a name.

326
00:30:05,400 --> 00:30:06,760
What name would you like?

327
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:10,400
I didn't quite get that.

328
00:30:12,760 --> 00:30:14,960
Brother Pietro would call him Piccolo.

329
00:30:15,840 --> 00:30:17,800
In a few weeks, he'll be about this big.

330
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:19,720
And anyway,
the name must begin with a B.

331
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:20,840
B?

332
00:30:21,240 --> 00:30:22,240
Why?

333
00:30:22,600 --> 00:30:23,640
That's just the way it is.

334
00:30:23,880 --> 00:30:26,840
Each litter needs to start with
a different initial letter.

335
00:30:27,120 --> 00:30:31,720
The last puppies were called
Alma, Achim, Arno and Alva.

336
00:30:32,200 --> 00:30:33,880
And now it's B's turn.

337
00:30:34,360 --> 00:30:37,000
B... B...

338
00:30:37,320 --> 00:30:38,880
How about Benno?

339
00:30:40,080 --> 00:30:41,240
Boring!

340
00:30:42,520 --> 00:30:44,240
Balthasar or...

341
00:30:44,760 --> 00:30:46,000
Bartholomew.

342
00:30:46,280 --> 00:30:47,760
Way too long, you can't shout that.

343
00:30:47,960 --> 00:30:49,720
Balthasar!

344
00:30:50,520 --> 00:30:53,360
Bartholomew!

345
00:30:53,880 --> 00:30:56,240
More like... Flash.

346
00:30:57,600 --> 00:30:59,080
Benedict?

347
00:30:59,720 --> 00:31:01,720
Heavens above!

348
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:06,680
What do you think of Biter?

349
00:31:07,000 --> 00:31:08,840
But he's not a biter, is he?

350
00:31:09,080 --> 00:31:10,240
Bear?

351
00:31:10,480 --> 00:31:12,600
What happens when a real bear shows up?

352
00:31:12,840 --> 00:31:14,200
And we call for the dog...

353
00:31:17,520 --> 00:31:19,000
What about... Barry?

354
00:31:19,640 --> 00:31:20,600
Barry?

355
00:31:20,760 --> 00:31:21,760
Yes, Barry.

356
00:31:22,120 --> 00:31:23,480
Fearless Barry.

357
00:31:24,080 --> 00:31:25,720
Barry the protector.

358
00:31:26,120 --> 00:31:27,120
Barry!

359
00:31:28,640 --> 00:31:29,640
Barry!

360
00:31:35,160 --> 00:31:36,400
Barry!

361
00:31:53,840 --> 00:31:55,600
Good morning, Barry.

362
00:31:59,920 --> 00:32:01,000
Hello, Barry.

363
00:32:02,880 --> 00:32:04,080
Did you sleep well?

364
00:32:16,240 --> 00:32:18,000
You have to be very quiet.

365
00:32:18,240 --> 00:32:19,560
No one must discover you.

366
00:32:20,360 --> 00:32:21,360
Okay?

367
00:32:21,600 --> 00:32:23,080
I'll be back.

368
00:32:31,320 --> 00:32:33,480
You can't come with me, Barry.

369
00:32:34,480 --> 00:32:35,600
You have to stay here.

370
00:32:35,880 --> 00:32:37,240
I haven't got time right now.

371
00:32:42,720 --> 00:32:44,760
Stay here and wait, okay?

372
00:32:45,120 --> 00:32:46,480
I'll be back soon.

373
00:33:19,880 --> 00:33:22,000
That's my book! Give it back.

374
00:33:22,200 --> 00:33:23,600
It was under the desk.

375
00:33:23,880 --> 00:33:26,360
Did I allow you to touch it
with your dirty fingers?

376
00:33:35,760 --> 00:33:37,000
Do you smell it too?

377
00:33:38,520 --> 00:33:40,000
And do you know what it is?

378
00:33:42,120 --> 00:33:43,040
You can't see it,

379
00:33:43,240 --> 00:33:44,680
but you can smell it.

380
00:33:45,080 --> 00:33:48,480
When you grow up with it,
it sticks to you.

381
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:52,360
You'll always be a country bumpkin
who stinks of cow dung.

382
00:33:52,840 --> 00:33:56,000
And no book in the world
will ever change that!

383
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:22,160
Italy.

384
00:34:43,840 --> 00:34:47,000
Does this lead south?

385
00:34:47,200 --> 00:34:51,480
Yes, when the snow has melted.

386
00:34:54,120 --> 00:34:56,600
Have you ever been there, in Italy?

387
00:35:00,840 --> 00:35:02,720
I came to Italy across the sea.

388
00:35:02,880 --> 00:35:04,640
From Africa.

389
00:35:06,360 --> 00:35:08,200
And why are you up here?

390
00:35:08,560 --> 00:35:10,480
I got a job at the hospice.

391
00:35:12,000 --> 00:35:13,800
No one up here has a problem

392
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:15,120
if your fur isn't white.

393
00:35:15,720 --> 00:35:16,960
Like with the dogs.

394
00:35:18,360 --> 00:35:19,840
It's the work that counts.

395
00:35:26,080 --> 00:35:27,360
Did you ever want to go back?

396
00:35:27,640 --> 00:35:28,600
Home?

397
00:35:33,000 --> 00:35:34,480
We've found a place here.

398
00:35:34,760 --> 00:35:35,840
Resi and I.

399
00:35:36,480 --> 00:35:37,440
If you're lucky,

400
00:35:38,080 --> 00:35:39,360
you will find yours too.

401
00:35:43,160 --> 00:35:44,640
Let's go!

402
00:35:47,840 --> 00:35:50,840
At these stone towers

403
00:35:51,120 --> 00:35:53,080
travellers can get their bearings.

404
00:35:53,320 --> 00:35:55,040
I thought the pass was closed?

405
00:35:55,240 --> 00:35:56,240
It is!

406
00:35:59,760 --> 00:36:07,000
A... A... Abor... Montal...

407
00:36:07,880 --> 00:36:10,120
Are you reading to Barry?

408
00:36:13,240 --> 00:36:14,880
Hey, Barry.

409
00:36:15,480 --> 00:36:17,120
I'm sure he likes it.

410
00:36:17,520 --> 00:36:19,880
Even though he can probably read better
than you.

411
00:36:20,480 --> 00:36:22,480
As if you could read.

412
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:32,840
<i>The streets are so clean</i>

413
00:36:33,120 --> 00:36:35,960
<i>that women walk there all year round</i>

414
00:36:36,240 --> 00:36:37,840
<i>in slippers.</i>

415
00:36:38,240 --> 00:36:40,200
<i>There are two rows of trees</i>

416
00:36:40,440 --> 00:36:42,720
<i>planted on both sides of the canals.</i>

417
00:36:50,640 --> 00:36:52,000
Did you never go to school?

418
00:36:53,600 --> 00:36:55,720
There's no teacher in our village.

419
00:36:56,520 --> 00:36:57,480
Sometimes

420
00:36:57,720 --> 00:36:59,600
the pastor taught us something

421
00:36:59,840 --> 00:37:04,000
when there wasn't much work to do
on the farms in winter.

422
00:37:06,240 --> 00:37:08,120
Come on, I'll show you.

423
00:37:10,160 --> 00:37:12,040
It's easier if you memorise

424
00:37:12,320 --> 00:37:14,040
the words as images.

425
00:37:14,240 --> 00:37:15,720
That's how I did it.

426
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:22,680
<i>If you want to travel
in the Netherlands,</i>

427
00:37:22,880 --> 00:37:24,600
<i>you do so on canals...</i>

428
00:37:24,840 --> 00:37:25,800
Why the Netherlands?

429
00:37:25,960 --> 00:37:27,440
The book's about Italy, isn't it?

430
00:37:27,640 --> 00:37:28,840
It's a travel book.

431
00:37:29,000 --> 00:37:30,000
From the Netherlands

432
00:37:30,240 --> 00:37:31,480
via Germany

433
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:33,200
and here, Switzerland,

434
00:37:33,360 --> 00:37:34,360
all the way to Italy.

435
00:37:35,760 --> 00:37:37,240
Why can you read?

436
00:37:37,640 --> 00:37:39,000
Because I learned it.

437
00:37:39,240 --> 00:37:40,720
From your mother?

438
00:37:43,760 --> 00:37:45,640
My mother has passed away.

439
00:37:47,880 --> 00:37:49,880
Brother Medicus taught me.

440
00:37:50,640 --> 00:37:51,880
I need to be able to read.

441
00:37:52,280 --> 00:37:53,840
I want to become a nurse.

442
00:37:54,120 --> 00:37:55,840
You're already a good nurse.

443
00:37:56,080 --> 00:37:57,040
I know.

444
00:37:59,120 --> 00:38:00,200
Shall we go on?

445
00:38:00,360 --> 00:38:01,480
Let's go on!

446
00:38:02,360 --> 00:38:13,120
<i>But in winter, the canals mark...</i>

447
00:38:13,360 --> 00:38:15,000
Great!

448
00:38:16,080 --> 00:38:17,880
Barry!

449
00:38:18,600 --> 00:38:26,080
<i>And so they were buried...</i>

450
00:38:27,240 --> 00:38:33,280
<i>The paths are not equally safe.</i>

451
00:38:34,360 --> 00:38:35,360
Barry!

452
00:38:36,040 --> 00:38:37,120
Now you want to play?

453
00:38:37,280 --> 00:38:38,360
Do you want to play?

454
00:38:42,880 --> 00:38:45,040
Aosta.

455
00:38:45,760 --> 00:38:46,840
Look, Barry!

456
00:38:47,080 --> 00:38:49,120
There's the sea.

457
00:38:49,320 --> 00:38:53,880
<i>And persuaded him by much coaxing</i>

458
00:38:54,080 --> 00:38:57,560
<i>to guide us to the island.</i>

459
00:39:27,760 --> 00:39:29,520
Avalanche!

460
00:39:31,600 --> 00:39:32,600
Avalanche!

461
00:39:40,000 --> 00:39:41,000
I'm coming with you!

462
00:39:41,080 --> 00:39:42,080
I can help!

463
00:39:42,240 --> 00:39:43,240
Julien!

464
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:46,320
We need all hands on deck.

465
00:39:46,600 --> 00:39:48,120
Fine. Go on.

466
00:40:03,560 --> 00:40:05,320
Where did the avalanche come down?

467
00:40:05,480 --> 00:40:06,480
Further down,

468
00:40:06,600 --> 00:40:07,960
on the Italian side.

469
00:40:34,160 --> 00:40:35,760
Julien, look! There!

470
00:40:38,160 --> 00:40:40,240
Search, Bella!
Yes!

471
00:40:40,360 --> 00:40:41,800
Here?

472
00:40:42,600 --> 00:40:43,720
Here is something!

473
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:45,080
Search!

474
00:40:45,360 --> 00:40:46,600
Look!

475
00:40:49,240 --> 00:40:51,080
-Schnell!
-Here!

476
00:40:54,880 --> 00:40:56,120
Here!

477
00:41:00,520 --> 00:41:01,480
Give me a hand!

478
00:41:02,360 --> 00:41:03,600
I've got him.

479
00:41:04,000 --> 00:41:05,360
Help pulling!

480
00:41:06,520 --> 00:41:07,480
Slowly. Be careful!

481
00:41:11,640 --> 00:41:12,640
Pull!

482
00:41:14,640 --> 00:41:16,240
I've got him!

483
00:41:17,720 --> 00:41:18,720
He's alive.

484
00:41:19,000 --> 00:41:20,240
Blanket!

485
00:41:23,360 --> 00:41:24,600
Are you alright?

486
00:41:24,800 --> 00:41:25,960
Can you talk to me?

487
00:41:26,440 --> 00:41:27,960
Thans. Thank you very much.

488
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:41,200
Well done!

489
00:41:45,880 --> 00:41:47,400
How many people are injured?

490
00:41:47,600 --> 00:41:48,560
I don't know!

491
00:41:48,720 --> 00:41:50,080
You'll have to ask Resi.

492
00:41:50,640 --> 00:41:51,640
Certainly not!

493
00:41:52,640 --> 00:41:54,600
George, you know where to put it.

494
00:41:56,120 --> 00:41:57,760
Here he comes.

495
00:42:00,400 --> 00:42:02,000
Who let him out?

496
00:42:07,360 --> 00:42:08,840
I'll take care of the dogs.

497
00:42:09,120 --> 00:42:10,680
You're off duty.

498
00:42:11,240 --> 00:42:12,240
George?

499
00:42:12,400 --> 00:42:13,360
Well done.

500
00:42:13,480 --> 00:42:15,120
We can use you up here.

501
00:42:17,000 --> 00:42:20,560
That country bumpkin's
so full of himself.

502
00:42:29,760 --> 00:42:31,480
Come on. Go now!

503
00:42:32,200 --> 00:42:33,680
Why? He hasn't harmed me.

504
00:42:34,000 --> 00:42:36,120
No one will find out that it was you.

505
00:42:36,400 --> 00:42:37,640
But I don't want to!

506
00:42:38,240 --> 00:42:39,840
Since when do you get to decide

507
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:42,560
what you want or don't want?

508
00:42:44,640 --> 00:42:45,720
Coward!

509
00:43:25,160 --> 00:43:26,360
Get off me, get off!

510
00:43:29,160 --> 00:43:30,520
What are you doing?

511
00:43:32,720 --> 00:43:33,720
Julien!

512
00:43:35,240 --> 00:43:37,360
Julien!

513
00:43:40,880 --> 00:43:42,720
George stole the dog!

514
00:43:43,000 --> 00:43:44,840
He hid it in his room!

515
00:43:45,200 --> 00:43:46,320
It was George!

516
00:43:47,520 --> 00:43:49,080
Where have you come from?

517
00:43:49,720 --> 00:43:51,200
George stole the dog!

518
00:43:56,520 --> 00:43:59,600
It is the Lord's will
that His creatures must die.

519
00:44:00,120 --> 00:44:02,240
And it is His will
when it should happen.

520
00:44:02,520 --> 00:44:05,640
This applies to us humans.
But it also applies to animals.

521
00:44:06,280 --> 00:44:07,880
That's not true, Prior.

522
00:44:09,200 --> 00:44:10,160
Oh, it isn't?

523
00:44:10,840 --> 00:44:11,840
If...

524
00:44:12,240 --> 00:44:13,720
If someone is in distress and...

525
00:44:14,000 --> 00:44:16,200
and we can help,

526
00:44:16,360 --> 00:44:19,080
then that's also God's will, isn't it?

527
00:44:19,880 --> 00:44:22,000
You said that we're here to serve.

528
00:44:24,880 --> 00:44:27,360
I didn't just feel sorry for him.

529
00:44:27,600 --> 00:44:28,760
Well, yes, that too.

530
00:44:29,000 --> 00:44:31,360
I felt sorry for him
when Stella didn't feed him.

531
00:44:32,000 --> 00:44:35,640
But he'll help a lot of people
when he grows up.

532
00:44:40,600 --> 00:44:41,600
George.

533
00:44:41,840 --> 00:44:45,320
Brother Benedict told me
that you stole this book

534
00:44:45,520 --> 00:44:48,000
from the library.

535
00:44:51,000 --> 00:44:52,440
What did you want to do with it?

536
00:44:55,200 --> 00:44:56,240
Answer!

537
00:44:59,560 --> 00:45:01,680
I wanted it so I could learn to read.

538
00:45:05,200 --> 00:45:06,480
Alright, then read.

539
00:45:16,520 --> 00:45:21,760
<i>When the sea was very rough,</i>

540
00:45:22,000 --> 00:45:26,760
<i>we came to a gondolier</i>

541
00:45:29,000 --> 00:45:36,280
<i>who was trying to pull his boat
out of the waves</i>

542
00:45:37,000 --> 00:45:38,360
<i>and we compelled him...</i>

543
00:45:38,520 --> 00:45:40,600
Okay. I think we got it.

544
00:45:45,720 --> 00:45:47,680
The dog will immediately
return to the barn,

545
00:45:47,880 --> 00:45:49,880
where it belongs, with its own kind.

546
00:45:50,120 --> 00:45:51,120
Barry.

547
00:45:51,200 --> 00:45:52,400
The dog's name's Barry.

548
00:45:53,280 --> 00:45:54,280
Barry...

549
00:45:57,160 --> 00:45:59,520
And you won't commit another offence.

550
00:45:59,680 --> 00:46:00,760
Do you understand?

551
00:46:01,640 --> 00:46:02,840
Yes, Prior.

552
00:46:06,640 --> 00:46:08,120
Brother Benedict...

553
00:46:08,400 --> 00:46:11,760
From now on, George will participate
in studies with the novices.

554
00:46:12,720 --> 00:46:13,680
Prior...!

555
00:46:13,840 --> 00:46:16,200
And do give him some decent clothes!

556
00:46:18,480 --> 00:46:19,800
You're right, George.

557
00:46:21,240 --> 00:46:22,960
We're here to serve.

558
00:46:30,640 --> 00:46:32,120
You lied to me.

559
00:46:32,360 --> 00:46:33,880
I didn't lie to you.

560
00:46:34,720 --> 00:46:37,000
I just didn't tell you everything.

561
00:46:39,400 --> 00:46:41,480
When did we stop
telling each other everything?

562
00:46:44,640 --> 00:46:45,760
Resi.

563
00:46:46,000 --> 00:46:47,600
What's wrong, darling?

564
00:46:48,080 --> 00:46:50,160
I don't like being alone all the time.

565
00:46:50,520 --> 00:46:51,840
You're not alone.

566
00:46:52,000 --> 00:46:54,760
Except for Pietro,
the monks don't talk with me.

567
00:46:54,960 --> 00:46:56,440
And the stupid novices...

568
00:46:56,600 --> 00:46:58,880
They just look down on me,
except when they have a scratch

569
00:46:59,120 --> 00:47:00,440
and need some ointment.

570
00:47:01,120 --> 00:47:02,080
And you...

571
00:47:02,440 --> 00:47:03,720
You're always working,

572
00:47:04,360 --> 00:47:06,720
in the stable or in the mountains.

573
00:47:08,000 --> 00:47:11,120
And in the evening,
when you come home, you're tired.

574
00:47:12,320 --> 00:47:14,240
Of course I'm alone.

575
00:47:14,640 --> 00:47:16,560
Ever since we've been here...

576
00:47:17,000 --> 00:47:19,120
Since Mom passed away.

577
00:47:23,000 --> 00:47:26,360
And now George is here
and I get on well with him.

578
00:47:36,040 --> 00:47:37,120
You two...

579
00:47:37,560 --> 00:47:39,320
You really had me fooled.

580
00:47:40,000 --> 00:47:43,080
And you even got a place at school.

581
00:47:45,600 --> 00:47:48,840
I want you to keep training Barry.

582
00:47:53,480 --> 00:47:55,240
Come on, get in there!

583
00:47:55,480 --> 00:47:56,600
Did you hear that, Barry?

584
00:47:56,800 --> 00:47:58,920
Listen carefully to what George
is going to tell you.

585
00:47:59,000 --> 00:48:01,000
I'll make a good dog out of you.

586
00:48:02,240 --> 00:48:04,240
You've done a good job.

587
00:48:04,720 --> 00:48:06,240
And I ate well.

588
00:48:06,480 --> 00:48:07,440
Of course!

589
00:48:09,640 --> 00:48:12,600
Study well and don't
be afraid of the novices.

590
00:48:13,400 --> 00:48:14,400
Oh no...!

591
00:48:27,720 --> 00:48:28,800
Gentlemen.

592
00:48:29,440 --> 00:48:31,200
He's supposed to be a novice now?

593
00:48:31,480 --> 00:48:33,000
Can a cow dance?

594
00:48:39,000 --> 00:48:40,000
Barry!

595
00:48:40,120 --> 00:48:41,720
Heavens above!

596
00:48:41,880 --> 00:48:43,120
I haven't got time now.

597
00:48:43,320 --> 00:48:45,160
I'll come back to you after school.

598
00:48:45,760 --> 00:48:46,760
Gentlemen!

599
00:49:01,200 --> 00:49:02,160
Silence.

600
00:49:05,880 --> 00:49:06,840
Gentlemen.

601
00:49:27,840 --> 00:49:29,760
Come here, Barry, come!

602
00:49:30,520 --> 00:49:31,480
Come!

603
00:49:37,400 --> 00:49:38,400
Sit, Barry!

604
00:49:40,280 --> 00:49:42,120
You have to obey now, Barry.

605
00:49:50,600 --> 00:49:52,240
Heavens above.

606
00:49:52,480 --> 00:49:54,600
Like a stork with a twisted beak.

607
00:49:57,760 --> 00:49:58,800
Go on.

608
00:50:12,000 --> 00:50:13,080
George!

609
00:50:14,080 --> 00:50:15,240
Would you like to try?

610
00:50:25,000 --> 00:50:25,960
Yes, good.

611
00:50:27,720 --> 00:50:29,800
You can sit on a cushion.

612
00:50:34,480 --> 00:50:37,320
This is a Moroccan tagine with lemon.

613
00:50:38,600 --> 00:50:40,000
How are things going at school?

614
00:50:40,200 --> 00:50:42,440
Heavens above!

615
00:50:43,320 --> 00:50:45,440
Do you want to be a teacher too?

616
00:50:45,640 --> 00:50:47,880
They're all so clever.

617
00:50:48,840 --> 00:50:50,440
Would you like to come too?

618
00:50:50,720 --> 00:50:52,360
Ask the prior.

619
00:50:52,880 --> 00:50:55,880
A girl among the novices.

620
00:50:56,880 --> 00:50:58,600
They" all become monks one day.

621
00:50:59,120 --> 00:51:02,000
And anyway, what would I do
among these clever monkeys?

622
00:51:03,000 --> 00:51:04,400
Soon you'll be one of them.

623
00:51:06,360 --> 00:51:07,600
I won't!

624
00:51:08,480 --> 00:51:09,480
Yes, you will!

625
00:51:09,600 --> 00:51:10,680
No, I won't!

626
00:51:37,640 --> 00:51:39,520
You can sleep at night.

627
00:51:43,400 --> 00:51:45,320
Listen. you have to work
especially hard

628
00:51:45,480 --> 00:51:48,800
otherwise you'll always be a farm boy.
Do you understand?

629
00:51:55,720 --> 00:51:57,240
-It's over, I won!
-Yeah...

630
00:51:57,680 --> 00:51:59,600
That's right, you cheated!

631
00:52:10,640 --> 00:52:13,000
What have we learned, Barry?
Come!

632
00:52:13,400 --> 00:52:16,880
Turn around, follow me.

633
00:52:21,720 --> 00:52:23,240
And now, sit!

634
00:52:23,840 --> 00:52:25,840
Well done!

635
00:52:26,880 --> 00:52:28,880
-Come, Bella. Come.
-Barry, come.

636
00:52:41,720 --> 00:52:43,240
Hey! Good man,

637
00:52:44,240 --> 00:52:45,840
You shouldn't rest here.

638
00:52:46,880 --> 00:52:48,600
My son is in Switzerland.

639
00:52:49,080 --> 00:52:50,600
Have to cross the pass.

640
00:52:50,880 --> 00:52:51,880
Come.

641
00:52:52,000 --> 00:52:54,200
Get some soup from the kitchen! Go on!

642
00:52:54,400 --> 00:52:55,360
-Hurry!
-Come, Barry!

643
00:53:00,120 --> 00:53:01,240
Hot!

644
00:53:04,000 --> 00:53:05,720
Don't spill everything on the table!

645
00:53:06,640 --> 00:53:07,840
Watch out!

646
00:53:10,720 --> 00:53:12,080
I don't have time!

647
00:53:14,080 --> 00:53:15,440
No time!

648
00:53:28,760 --> 00:53:30,120
No, Barry, wait!

649
00:53:39,360 --> 00:53:42,360
Is there anything left in the bottle?

650
00:53:44,000 --> 00:53:45,360
I'm sorry.

651
00:53:51,280 --> 00:53:53,800
That mustn't happen to you again!

652
00:53:54,480 --> 00:53:55,480
Come on!

653
00:54:19,120 --> 00:54:20,320
Come, Barry!

654
00:54:29,280 --> 00:54:30,640
What's he doing?

655
00:54:30,880 --> 00:54:32,640
He doesn't seem to be hungry.

656
00:54:45,760 --> 00:54:46,840
Barry, come to me.

657
00:54:48,320 --> 00:54:49,800
Just try it on. Come on!

658
00:54:50,000 --> 00:54:52,440
If it doesn't fit,
I'll take it off again.

659
00:54:53,640 --> 00:54:54,720
Very good.

660
00:54:55,000 --> 00:54:56,360
What do you think, Barry?

661
00:54:57,880 --> 00:54:59,440
Now the soup can't spill anymore.

662
00:54:59,880 --> 00:55:01,840
Even if the rescuers are slow

663
00:55:02,000 --> 00:55:03,640
or get stuck somewhere.

664
00:55:05,640 --> 00:55:07,480
Or stumble, like I did.

665
00:55:10,880 --> 00:55:12,040
Yes, Barry.

666
00:55:23,600 --> 00:55:24,600
George?

667
00:55:26,480 --> 00:55:28,000
For you.

668
00:55:28,240 --> 00:55:29,240
For me?

669
00:55:29,360 --> 00:55:30,440
From Italy.

670
00:55:36,720 --> 00:55:37,760
Dear George,

671
00:55:37,960 --> 00:55:40,480
A comrade is writing this letter for me.

672
00:55:40,760 --> 00:55:43,360
Perhaps a monk will read it to you.

673
00:55:43,640 --> 00:55:46,240
I hope the stone snail
has brought you luck.

674
00:55:46,640 --> 00:55:49,640
I'm sorry I couldn't stay with you.

675
00:55:50,120 --> 00:55:53,240
Imagine,
the Austrians promised me more pay

676
00:55:53,480 --> 00:55:55,760
than the two of us can earn in a year.

677
00:55:57,800 --> 00:56:00,480
As a soldier, I got boots and a gun.

678
00:56:01,360 --> 00:56:03,360
We're waiting for the war to start

679
00:56:03,560 --> 00:56:05,240
against the French.

680
00:56:05,440 --> 00:56:08,000
We have lots of time and little food.

681
00:56:08,840 --> 00:56:10,360
When the war is over,

682
00:56:10,600 --> 00:56:11,840
I'll come and get you.

683
00:56:12,120 --> 00:56:13,120
Alfons.

684
00:56:32,760 --> 00:56:34,000
George.

685
00:56:49,480 --> 00:56:51,840
We'll show him
what we're capable of.

686
00:56:58,200 --> 00:56:59,200
What's going on?

687
00:56:59,320 --> 00:57:00,360
What's this?

688
00:57:00,680 --> 00:57:01,640
Give it back.

689
00:57:01,800 --> 00:57:03,200
-Oh, a love letter!
-Give it back!

690
00:57:07,120 --> 00:57:08,120
Give it back!

691
00:57:11,760 --> 00:57:14,200
Oh! From the brave soldier
who abandoned you.

692
00:57:14,400 --> 00:57:16,000
My family's none of your business.

693
00:57:16,240 --> 00:57:17,760
A soldier in the Austrian army...

694
00:57:18,280 --> 00:57:19,400
That's what you call family?

695
00:57:19,600 --> 00:57:20,960
And where's your family?

696
00:57:21,240 --> 00:57:22,560
Why are you up here?

697
00:57:22,800 --> 00:57:23,800
My family...

698
00:57:28,720 --> 00:57:30,960
My family pays for everything here.

699
00:57:31,240 --> 00:57:34,000
You're being fed here
thanks to my family.

700
00:57:34,240 --> 00:57:36,760
That you don't have to sleep in a pigsty
is thanks to my family.

701
00:57:40,720 --> 00:57:42,360
You country bumpkin!

702
00:57:53,000 --> 00:57:54,720
Is spring finally coming?

703
00:57:54,880 --> 00:57:57,240
The spring storms will come first.

704
00:57:57,480 --> 00:58:00,200
The worst of the cold weather is over.
But the avalanches...

705
00:58:00,360 --> 00:58:01,360
Stay together.

706
00:58:01,480 --> 00:58:03,720
The snow's unpredictable
when it gets warmer.

707
00:58:06,000 --> 00:58:08,240
But he can become quite unpleasant.

708
00:58:08,440 --> 00:58:12,480
If Brother Benedict gives you a mean
look, the class immediately freezes.

709
00:58:13,600 --> 00:58:17,080
But he's a nice teacher as long as...

710
00:58:17,240 --> 00:58:19,040
Hey! A wolf.

711
00:58:19,360 --> 00:58:20,360
A wolf!

712
00:58:20,960 --> 00:58:22,040
Go behind the rocks!

713
00:58:23,000 --> 00:58:24,840
Barry! Come back here.

714
00:58:25,360 --> 00:58:26,360
Come on, George!

715
00:58:26,520 --> 00:58:28,120
-Leave the dog alone!
-Barry!

716
00:58:28,400 --> 00:58:29,360
Come back!

717
00:58:29,760 --> 00:58:30,760
Come on, George!

718
00:58:31,840 --> 00:58:32,880
Come back!

719
00:58:34,120 --> 00:58:35,120
He won't harm us.

720
00:59:06,760 --> 00:59:07,760
George.

721
00:59:08,760 --> 00:59:09,800
-Everything okay?
-George!

722
00:59:09,880 --> 00:59:11,120
Well done, Barry!

723
00:59:11,480 --> 00:59:12,920
-George, everything okay?
-Yes.

724
00:59:13,080 --> 00:59:15,000
-How did you do this?
-What did you do?

725
00:59:15,200 --> 00:59:17,240
No, how did you do that?

726
00:59:17,640 --> 00:59:19,120
I don't know.

727
00:59:31,480 --> 00:59:35,080
You know that this was dangerous,
what you did up there.

728
00:59:36,440 --> 00:59:38,120
We trusted each other.

729
00:59:41,640 --> 00:59:43,720
You've made a good dog out of him.

730
00:59:45,000 --> 00:59:46,560
He's the best!

731
01:00:00,400 --> 01:00:01,600
For you.

732
01:00:05,840 --> 01:00:07,000
Thank you.

733
01:00:09,200 --> 01:00:11,560
I prayed that something would happen.

734
01:00:11,720 --> 01:00:14,080
-Like that a rock would fall on the wolf.
-And suddenly...

735
01:00:14,440 --> 01:00:16,000
it became dead quiet.

736
01:00:16,200 --> 01:00:18,640
George and Barry... they just
stood there, in front of a wolf.

737
01:00:18,880 --> 01:00:20,720
-A real wolf?
-The atmosphere was very strange.

738
01:00:20,840 --> 01:00:22,680
George! Come over here.

739
01:00:23,200 --> 01:00:24,600
So small, but so brave!

740
01:00:24,880 --> 01:00:26,880
I almost wet my pants.

741
01:00:28,600 --> 01:00:30,560
I'd never have dared to do that.

742
01:00:49,600 --> 01:00:51,800
The French are coming!

743
01:00:53,120 --> 01:00:55,360
Napoleon's soldiers!

744
01:00:59,360 --> 01:01:02,520
A little dignity, gentlemen. Dignity!

745
01:01:04,160 --> 01:01:05,160
Good evening, captain.

746
01:01:05,320 --> 01:01:09,280
Welcome to our hospice.
How many soldiers are you?

747
01:01:09,440 --> 01:01:12,880
For the moment just my section.
But others will come.

748
01:01:13,520 --> 01:01:15,760
How can you even talk to them?

749
01:01:16,400 --> 01:01:17,680
In French.

750
01:01:20,480 --> 01:01:23,440
It doesn't matter where they're from.
We're giving them shelter.

751
01:01:23,840 --> 01:01:25,080
That's what the hospice is for.

752
01:01:25,240 --> 01:01:26,640
But they're soldiers.

753
01:01:26,880 --> 01:01:27,880
Frenchmen!

754
01:01:28,000 --> 01:01:30,240
They destroy everything in their path.

755
01:01:32,000 --> 01:01:33,840
Your brother's a soldier too.

756
01:01:56,760 --> 01:02:00,200
Alfons is out there
and he's going to fight the French.

757
01:02:00,880 --> 01:02:02,360
And I don't know if he...

758
01:02:03,360 --> 01:02:05,240
He doesn't have the stone snail anymore.

759
01:02:05,520 --> 01:02:07,520
It always brought him luck.

760
01:02:07,880 --> 01:02:09,400
Now I have it.

761
01:02:10,840 --> 01:02:13,440
He'll run away if it gets dangerous.

762
01:02:14,360 --> 01:02:15,960
Do you think so?

763
01:02:18,200 --> 01:02:20,720
Yes. He runs away and comes back to you.

764
01:02:21,000 --> 01:02:22,240
Everything will be fine.

765
01:02:37,240 --> 01:02:40,120
We have to leave at dawn

766
01:02:40,360 --> 01:02:43,640
otherwise we won't get to the wedding
in Italy by daylight.

767
01:02:44,600 --> 01:02:46,120
That's Celestin's father,

768
01:02:46,400 --> 01:02:47,520
Mr von Wydler,

769
01:02:47,760 --> 01:02:48,840
and his sister,

770
01:02:49,000 --> 01:02:50,120
Miss Florence.

771
01:02:50,520 --> 01:02:53,120
Tomorrow, everyone will
travel on to Italy for a wedding.

772
01:02:53,360 --> 01:02:54,600
Celestin too?

773
01:02:59,560 --> 01:03:01,040
...out there in the wild valleys,

774
01:03:01,240 --> 01:03:02,240
in wind and weather.

775
01:03:03,000 --> 01:03:03,960
Just a few days ago

776
01:03:04,200 --> 01:03:06,040
we rescued a group of poor pilgrims,

777
01:03:06,200 --> 01:03:07,120
when suddenly

778
01:03:07,280 --> 01:03:09,360
a huge wolf stood in front of me.

779
01:03:10,240 --> 01:03:13,000
A huge animal with bulging eyes

780
01:03:13,240 --> 01:03:14,840
and enormous teeth.

781
01:03:15,120 --> 01:03:18,000
I ordered Barry to stand with me
in front of the wolf.

782
01:03:18,200 --> 01:03:19,720
The wolf was so confused,

783
01:03:19,880 --> 01:03:22,760
that he tucked his tail between his legs
and ran away.

784
01:03:22,960 --> 01:03:24,760
You should have seen that.

785
01:03:35,280 --> 01:03:38,120
Would you like to see Barry?

786
01:03:39,320 --> 01:03:41,360
Father, may I go with him?

787
01:03:42,040 --> 01:03:43,840
If Brother Benedict allows you to.

788
01:03:44,120 --> 01:03:45,960
He has relieved me of my duties.

789
01:03:50,600 --> 01:03:52,720
Hey, you fool!

790
01:03:53,600 --> 01:03:54,880
I'm sorry!

791
01:03:55,120 --> 01:03:56,600
Hurry up and clean that up!

792
01:04:04,240 --> 01:04:06,840
Move. Come on! Get up!

793
01:04:07,000 --> 01:04:09,120
-You're hurting him!
-You have to show them who's boss.

794
01:04:09,240 --> 01:04:10,800
That's the only way they'll obey.

795
01:04:10,960 --> 01:04:12,200
Stupid animal!

796
01:04:16,400 --> 01:04:17,720
Sit! Off!

797
01:04:24,600 --> 01:04:25,840
Stupid animal!

798
01:04:27,360 --> 01:04:28,360
Get out!

799
01:04:31,480 --> 01:04:32,480
Get out!

800
01:04:35,440 --> 01:04:36,880
Come on, Florence!

801
01:04:37,120 --> 01:04:39,000
Let's leave this country bumpkin.

802
01:04:44,080 --> 01:04:45,080
Are you alright?

803
01:04:45,200 --> 01:04:46,960
-Do you want to pet him?
-Is he...

804
01:04:47,400 --> 01:04:48,880
-May I?
-Yes.

805
01:04:55,280 --> 01:04:56,880
He's very well-behaved!

806
01:04:57,160 --> 01:04:58,880
Barry's the best dog in the world.

807
01:04:59,520 --> 01:05:00,960
If I had a dog,

808
01:05:01,200 --> 01:05:02,720
I'd never hit it.

809
01:05:03,240 --> 01:05:05,360
It would have to be just like Barry.

810
01:05:07,880 --> 01:05:10,480
We'd be friends, you and me.

811
01:05:10,680 --> 01:05:11,720
Best friends.

812
01:05:31,280 --> 01:05:32,760
Why do you need that?

813
01:05:37,760 --> 01:05:39,240
For the journey.

814
01:05:49,880 --> 01:05:50,840
Where is he?

815
01:05:54,000 --> 01:05:55,440
I couldn't do anything, George.

816
01:05:55,600 --> 01:05:56,840
Where's Barry?

817
01:05:57,120 --> 01:05:58,600
In the stable,
with the soldiers.

818
01:05:58,800 --> 01:06:00,360
He's going with Florence tomorrow.

819
01:06:00,600 --> 01:06:01,760
He belongs here!

820
01:06:02,000 --> 01:06:03,080
In the mountains!

821
01:06:06,360 --> 01:06:09,080
Von Wydler is an influential man.

822
01:06:09,600 --> 01:06:11,120
Florence will take good care of him.

823
01:06:11,400 --> 01:06:12,360
You don't know that!

824
01:06:12,520 --> 01:06:13,880
They may not take Barry away.

825
01:06:14,120 --> 01:06:16,080
George, choose another dog.

826
01:06:16,280 --> 01:06:17,240
No!

827
01:06:18,000 --> 01:06:19,000
George!

828
01:06:22,520 --> 01:06:23,480
Pietro!

829
01:06:24,240 --> 01:06:25,360
Pietro!

830
01:07:03,720 --> 01:07:04,720
Barry.

831
01:07:26,200 --> 01:07:27,240
Barry.

832
01:07:29,000 --> 01:07:30,360
Let's go away.

833
01:07:30,640 --> 01:07:32,640
But you have to be quiet.

834
01:07:36,560 --> 01:07:37,560
Barry.

835
01:07:38,600 --> 01:07:39,600
Quiet.

836
01:07:42,680 --> 01:07:43,680
Barry.

837
01:07:44,960 --> 01:07:45,960
Come.

838
01:07:57,760 --> 01:07:58,760
Sit!

839
01:07:59,720 --> 01:08:00,680
Wait!

840
01:08:38,400 --> 01:08:40,120
They want to take him away from me.

841
01:08:40,760 --> 01:08:42,320
And where are you going now?

842
01:08:44,000 --> 01:08:45,520
They won't take you back.

843
01:08:45,720 --> 01:08:47,000
I'm going to Alfons.

844
01:08:47,480 --> 01:08:48,480
Into war?

845
01:08:51,000 --> 01:08:52,320
I don't want you to...

846
01:08:53,120 --> 01:08:54,840
not be here anymore.

847
01:08:55,000 --> 01:08:56,360
I have to go, Resi.

848
01:08:59,400 --> 01:09:01,560
Do you have your lucky charm?
The stone snail?

849
01:09:07,400 --> 01:09:09,240
Take care of yourself.

850
01:09:12,240 --> 01:09:13,480
Goodbye, Barry.

851
01:09:19,480 --> 01:09:20,480
Barry, come!

852
01:10:10,000 --> 01:10:11,320
We're almost there, Barry.

853
01:10:12,120 --> 01:10:15,480
We just have to make it to the hut.

854
01:10:33,040 --> 01:10:35,800
Come, get in here!

855
01:10:36,000 --> 01:10:37,720
We'll be safe here until tomorrow.

856
01:10:38,720 --> 01:10:40,120
I know you're hungry too!

857
01:10:47,880 --> 01:10:49,560
Everything's fine.

858
01:10:54,760 --> 01:10:56,200
Look, Barry. This...

859
01:10:56,360 --> 01:10:57,360
is Verona.

860
01:10:57,640 --> 01:10:58,720
Alfons is here.

861
01:10:59,000 --> 01:11:00,640
And we're here, in Switzerland.

862
01:11:00,880 --> 01:11:02,200
With a few big jumps

863
01:11:02,520 --> 01:11:04,080
we'll be there.

864
01:11:04,480 --> 01:11:06,320
And if there's not too
much snow in Italy,

865
01:11:06,400 --> 01:11:08,200
we'll manage to get there in ten days.

866
01:11:35,000 --> 01:11:37,600
It's madness to set off in this fog!

867
01:11:38,120 --> 01:11:40,600
I told them to wait another day.

868
01:11:42,000 --> 01:11:44,640
But Mr von Wydler wouldn't listen.

869
01:12:05,120 --> 01:12:06,120
Damn!

870
01:12:07,240 --> 01:12:09,120
Barry, we overslept.

871
01:12:21,240 --> 01:12:23,240
Barry, don't pull so hard!

872
01:12:31,000 --> 01:12:32,600
Hey, what's the matter?

873
01:12:34,520 --> 01:12:35,760
Barry!

874
01:12:37,760 --> 01:12:38,720
Barry!

875
01:12:44,080 --> 01:12:45,040
Barry!

876
01:12:49,440 --> 01:12:50,720
Barry!

877
01:12:57,640 --> 01:12:58,720
Barry!

878
01:13:03,000 --> 01:13:04,120
Barry!

879
01:13:23,360 --> 01:13:25,200
Barry, here you are!

880
01:13:30,000 --> 01:13:30,960
You?

881
01:13:33,760 --> 01:13:35,000
Where are the others?

882
01:13:35,360 --> 01:13:37,480
Florence, and your father?

883
01:13:39,120 --> 01:13:41,000
Did he abandon you here?

884
01:13:41,720 --> 01:13:43,640
Certainly not, you idiot!

885
01:13:45,240 --> 01:13:46,240
Come on!

886
01:13:46,640 --> 01:13:47,640
No!

887
01:13:47,880 --> 01:13:49,120
I'm staying here!

888
01:13:49,400 --> 01:13:50,480
They'll find me.

889
01:13:50,880 --> 01:13:52,640
I'm Celestin von Wydler.

890
01:13:54,640 --> 01:13:57,240
You're nobody out here.
Do you understand?

891
01:13:57,720 --> 01:14:00,360
Come on,
I'll help you get down to the valley.

892
01:14:00,880 --> 01:14:02,360
Leave me alone!

893
01:14:02,560 --> 01:14:03,600
I'm not afraid!

894
01:14:06,440 --> 01:14:09,680
Fine, we'll go on to Italy without you.

895
01:14:10,120 --> 01:14:11,240
Barry.

896
01:14:13,760 --> 01:14:15,200
Come on, Barry, let's go.

897
01:14:32,080 --> 01:14:33,840
Is this even the right way?

898
01:14:36,400 --> 01:14:38,480
You have no idea where we are!

899
01:14:42,600 --> 01:14:44,360
I knew it was you.

900
01:14:44,600 --> 01:14:45,720
Who stole the animal.

901
01:14:46,240 --> 01:14:49,080
You mean Barry, who found you?

902
01:15:03,120 --> 01:15:04,320
We're lost!

903
01:15:04,520 --> 01:15:05,600
You and your damn dog.

904
01:15:05,840 --> 01:15:07,720
We need shelter from the storm.

905
01:15:08,000 --> 01:15:09,880
We have to trust Barry!

906
01:15:15,760 --> 01:15:17,760
I can't go on! My leg.

907
01:15:17,960 --> 01:15:18,960
It's too much.

908
01:15:19,640 --> 01:15:20,640
Come on!

909
01:15:21,400 --> 01:15:22,840
Pull yourself together!

910
01:15:33,480 --> 01:15:35,360
Well done, Barry!

911
01:15:36,360 --> 01:15:39,120
Go ahead. I'll be right there!

912
01:15:39,760 --> 01:15:41,000
Where are you going?

913
01:15:45,120 --> 01:15:46,480
Keep going, Barry.

914
01:16:20,080 --> 01:16:22,240
Are you crazy? The book's valuable!

915
01:16:22,480 --> 01:16:24,320
Would you rather freeze to death?

916
01:16:42,600 --> 01:16:44,120
Where are we?

917
01:16:44,760 --> 01:16:46,760
Somewhere under a glacier.

918
01:17:19,480 --> 01:17:21,080
That was your idea,

919
01:17:21,400 --> 01:17:22,760
about Barry.

920
01:17:24,760 --> 01:17:26,600
Florence would have taken
good care of him.

921
01:17:26,760 --> 01:17:27,760
I know that.

922
01:17:27,960 --> 01:17:29,840
But you wanted to take
Barry away from me.

923
01:17:30,360 --> 01:17:31,960
Even though you already have everything.

924
01:17:32,200 --> 01:17:33,480
You have got everything!

925
01:17:34,080 --> 01:17:35,560
Everyone likes you.

926
01:17:37,120 --> 01:17:38,360
Julien, Resi

927
01:17:39,000 --> 01:17:40,240
and you're good with the dogs.

928
01:17:40,600 --> 01:17:42,600
Even Matteo is now your friend.

929
01:17:43,480 --> 01:17:45,320
Since you've arrived...

930
01:17:46,120 --> 01:17:49,120
everyone has begun... to shine.

931
01:17:55,480 --> 01:17:58,480
Why didn't you turn back
when the storm started?

932
01:18:02,200 --> 01:18:05,000
My father said that the weather
would get better in the valley.

933
01:18:05,640 --> 01:18:07,360
And the porters didn't say anything?

934
01:18:07,640 --> 01:18:09,120
They didn't resist?

935
01:18:09,360 --> 01:18:10,840
You don't know my father.

936
01:18:13,600 --> 01:18:15,960
My father only sees his business

937
01:18:17,200 --> 01:18:20,120
and Florence with her pretty face.

938
01:18:20,720 --> 01:18:23,720
And my brother,
with his fiancée in Milan.

939
01:18:25,360 --> 01:18:27,360
I wouldn't want to see myself either.

940
01:18:28,840 --> 01:18:31,600
An ugly weakling with a crippled leg.

941
01:18:35,240 --> 01:18:37,000
You're not ugly.

942
01:18:38,520 --> 01:18:40,360
Only when you're mean.

943
01:19:02,440 --> 01:19:03,440
Barry.

944
01:19:03,600 --> 01:19:06,120
Celestin doesn't make it to the valley.

945
01:19:06,560 --> 01:19:08,240
We have to go back to the hospice.

946
01:19:09,000 --> 01:19:11,000
And when we get back,

947
01:19:11,320 --> 01:19:13,120
we can no longer be together.

948
01:19:16,000 --> 01:19:18,600
Then you have to go with Florence.

949
01:20:32,000 --> 01:20:33,720
My father will never find us here.

950
01:20:34,440 --> 01:20:35,440
Right?

951
01:20:37,000 --> 01:20:39,240
No one will find us in here.

952
01:20:48,960 --> 01:20:49,960
Barry!

953
01:20:54,760 --> 01:20:55,760
Come!

954
01:21:32,360 --> 01:21:34,200
This has to lead somewhere.

955
01:21:36,280 --> 01:21:38,080
But look...

956
01:21:38,400 --> 01:21:39,640
We can't even really stand.

957
01:21:39,840 --> 01:21:41,360
How are you going to climb down there?

958
01:21:41,480 --> 01:21:42,960
With all that ice?

959
01:21:46,600 --> 01:21:48,120
Not climbing...

960
01:21:51,280 --> 01:21:52,320
Are you scared?

961
01:21:52,480 --> 01:21:53,520
Of course!

962
01:21:54,320 --> 01:21:55,320
Me too.

963
01:22:01,120 --> 01:22:02,120
One...

964
01:22:06,080 --> 01:22:07,080
two...

965
01:22:44,000 --> 01:22:45,000
Barry!

966
01:22:46,160 --> 01:22:47,200
Come, Barry.

967
01:22:50,880 --> 01:22:51,880
Thanks!

968
01:22:53,880 --> 01:22:54,880
Look!

969
01:23:29,880 --> 01:23:30,880
I can't go on.

970
01:23:31,040 --> 01:23:32,080
Come on!

971
01:23:32,240 --> 01:23:33,480
We're almost there.

972
01:23:33,640 --> 01:23:34,640
It's not far now.

973
01:23:34,840 --> 01:23:36,000
You can hold on to Barry.

974
01:24:27,600 --> 01:24:28,960
Holy Mother of God!

975
01:24:29,240 --> 01:24:30,400
Help!

976
01:24:43,240 --> 01:24:44,320
Celestin!

977
01:24:45,240 --> 01:24:46,240
My son!

978
01:24:46,880 --> 01:24:48,000
Help!

979
01:24:50,240 --> 01:24:51,600
Dad.

980
01:24:55,000 --> 01:24:56,080
George!

981
01:24:57,120 --> 01:24:58,120
George!

982
01:24:59,360 --> 01:25:00,320
Thank God!

983
01:25:01,920 --> 01:25:03,000
Hang in there!

984
01:25:03,200 --> 01:25:04,480
Everything will be fine.

985
01:25:05,880 --> 01:25:08,000
I'm so glad you're back!

986
01:25:09,840 --> 01:25:11,360
Everything will be fine.

987
01:25:21,480 --> 01:25:24,240
You've only got a sprained foot
and a few frostbitten toes.

988
01:25:26,360 --> 01:25:28,200
Where's Barry?

989
01:25:30,640 --> 01:25:32,320
This is a hospital room, you idiot!

990
01:25:32,520 --> 01:25:34,320
Sorry.
I have to take George to the prior.

991
01:25:34,520 --> 01:25:35,480
Now?

992
01:25:35,600 --> 01:25:38,040
Mr von Wydler and his daughter
want to continue their journey.

993
01:26:00,120 --> 01:26:01,840
I hear you're well.

994
01:26:02,840 --> 01:26:04,000
I'm glad to hear it.

995
01:26:07,360 --> 01:26:09,080
You stole, George.

996
01:26:09,240 --> 01:26:11,600
And from a patron of
the monastery at that.

997
01:26:13,240 --> 01:26:15,000
What do you have to say about that?

998
01:26:17,240 --> 01:26:19,240
I didn't want Barry
to have to live in a town.

999
01:26:20,720 --> 01:26:22,520
I wanted him to stay up here.

1000
01:26:22,760 --> 01:26:24,520
You broke the rules again.

1001
01:26:24,760 --> 01:26:26,640
Prior, with all due respect.

1002
01:26:26,880 --> 01:26:28,360
George saved his comrade's life.

1003
01:26:28,520 --> 01:26:29,520
Yes.

1004
01:26:29,600 --> 01:26:32,480
You have shown courage and humanity.

1005
01:26:33,360 --> 01:26:35,080
I therefore refrain from punishment.

1006
01:26:36,480 --> 01:26:37,480
May I...

1007
01:26:37,840 --> 01:26:39,560
say goodbye to Barry?

1008
01:26:40,200 --> 01:26:41,200
George.

1009
01:26:42,480 --> 01:26:44,560
You brought back my son.

1010
01:26:45,000 --> 01:26:47,080
I can't thank you enough for that.

1011
01:26:47,880 --> 01:26:49,120
So...

1012
01:26:50,840 --> 01:26:52,240
Barry belongs to you.

1013
01:26:52,880 --> 01:26:54,720
And you belong to him.

1014
01:26:58,880 --> 01:27:01,600
I'm sorry I wanted to take him away
from you.

1015
01:27:07,280 --> 01:27:08,240
Thank you.

1016
01:27:08,360 --> 01:27:09,600
One more thing, George.

1017
01:27:10,520 --> 01:27:13,120
We've decided to accept you as a novice.

1018
01:27:13,640 --> 01:27:16,120
Mr von Wydler will cover the costs
of your education.

1019
01:27:16,320 --> 01:27:18,720
In three years you can join the Order

1020
01:27:19,000 --> 01:27:20,320
and become a priest.

1021
01:27:22,440 --> 01:27:24,000
I don't want to become a priest.

1022
01:27:24,480 --> 01:27:26,120
Heavens above... George!

1023
01:27:26,280 --> 01:27:27,360
I'd like to teach

1024
01:27:27,520 --> 01:27:29,200
the children in my village

1025
01:27:29,360 --> 01:27:31,000
everything I've learned here at school.

1026
01:27:33,640 --> 01:27:35,360
You want to become a teacher?

1027
01:27:37,600 --> 01:27:38,880
Well...

1028
01:27:41,840 --> 01:27:44,880
Well.
That should be fine with our rules,

1029
01:27:45,080 --> 01:27:48,240
that you continue to attend classes
with us

1030
01:27:48,480 --> 01:27:50,320
and become a good teacher.

1031
01:27:53,400 --> 01:27:55,560
Barry! Hello!

1032
01:27:56,920 --> 01:27:58,080
Hello.

1033
01:27:59,600 --> 01:28:02,640
I thought I'd never see you again.

1034
01:28:05,120 --> 01:28:06,600
Come, Celestin.

1035
01:28:08,840 --> 01:28:10,960
-Yes, Barry.
-A fine dog.

1036
01:28:11,120 --> 01:28:15,520
-Barry, you're the best dog in the world!
-You're such a good dog.

1037
01:28:15,840 --> 01:28:17,240
Did you miss me already?

1038
01:28:18,120 --> 01:28:19,120
George?

1039
01:28:20,760 --> 01:28:22,000
Alfons!

1040
01:28:26,720 --> 01:28:28,200
Is the war over?

1041
01:28:28,480 --> 01:28:29,440
I don't know.

1042
01:28:29,600 --> 01:28:31,400
But it's not my war anymore.

1043
01:28:33,640 --> 01:28:35,120
-This is Resi.
-Hello.

1044
01:28:35,640 --> 01:28:37,120
-This is Celestin.
-Hello.

1045
01:28:37,360 --> 01:28:38,320
And this

1046
01:28:38,720 --> 01:28:39,960
is my friend Barry.

1047
01:28:42,800 --> 01:28:44,680
I told you he was going to run away.

1048
01:28:45,120 --> 01:28:46,120
Come!

1049
01:28:46,200 --> 01:28:48,240
I'll take you to Brother Pietro
in the kitchen.

1050
01:28:52,560 --> 01:28:55,240
We won't let your brother go hungry.

1051
01:28:56,120 --> 01:28:57,120
Enjoy your meal.

1052
01:29:05,360 --> 01:29:07,520
Do you think I can rest for a bit here?

1053
01:29:07,880 --> 01:29:09,600
Before we set off on our way?

1054
01:29:10,720 --> 01:29:12,000
On our way?

1055
01:29:12,520 --> 01:29:13,760
Home, to the farm.

1056
01:29:14,000 --> 01:29:15,240
We'll rebuild it.

1057
01:29:20,720 --> 01:29:21,840
I'm staying here.

1058
01:29:24,440 --> 01:29:25,560
What?

1059
01:29:26,840 --> 01:29:28,480
You want to stay up here?

1060
01:29:29,240 --> 01:29:30,560
There's nothing here!

1061
01:29:30,760 --> 01:29:32,000
Just snow and ice!

1062
01:29:32,240 --> 01:29:33,560
I'm going to school here.

1063
01:29:33,760 --> 01:29:34,840
With the novices.

1064
01:29:35,000 --> 01:29:37,320
And I'll make sure he stays well-behaved
and focused!

1065
01:29:38,000 --> 01:29:40,320
I will follow you to our village,

1066
01:29:40,760 --> 01:29:42,240
as soon as I've become a teacher.

1067
01:29:49,200 --> 01:29:50,840
George the teacher...

1068
01:29:53,640 --> 01:29:56,120
I always knew you'd turn out to be
a remarkable person.

1069
01:29:57,280 --> 01:29:59,120
It brings good luck, doesn't it?

1070
01:29:59,400 --> 01:30:00,640
The stone snail?

1071
01:30:00,880 --> 01:30:03,200
Actually, it's not a stone snail,

1072
01:30:04,120 --> 01:30:06,080
it's an ammonite.

1073
01:30:09,600 --> 01:30:10,600
Nerd!

1074
01:30:13,880 --> 01:30:16,400
Do you think others
will also return to the village?

1075
01:30:16,520 --> 01:30:17,480
We'll see.

1076
01:30:17,640 --> 01:30:20,280
-They won't all have become rich abroad.
-Like you, you mean?

1077
01:30:20,560 --> 01:30:21,520
Hey!

1078
01:30:24,120 --> 01:30:25,120
First,

1079
01:30:25,200 --> 01:30:26,880
I'll rebuild the stable.

1080
01:30:27,080 --> 01:30:28,800
I can shelter with the animals.

1081
01:30:28,960 --> 01:30:31,000
And next winter, I'll rebuild the house.

1082
01:30:31,400 --> 01:30:33,760
And then you'll soon be home.

1083
01:30:42,480 --> 01:30:43,720
Are you sure?

1084
01:30:44,360 --> 01:30:46,240
I have everything I need.

1085
01:30:48,240 --> 01:30:49,320
See you soon.

1086
01:30:58,200 --> 01:30:59,240
And you,

1087
01:30:59,640 --> 01:31:00,960
take care of my brother.

1088
01:31:01,320 --> 01:31:03,280
Take good care of him, alright?

1089
01:31:07,640 --> 01:31:08,960
Come, Barry.

1090
01:31:20,280 --> 01:31:21,360
Alfons!

1091
01:31:21,880 --> 01:31:24,800
When I'm a teacher, I'll come home.

1092
01:31:41,720 --> 01:31:47,560
BARRY LIVED FROM 1800 TO 1814.

1093
01:31:47,760 --> 01:31:53,640
HE RESCUED THE LIVES OF 40 PEOPLE.

